### Steps to reproduce

Steps:
1. Open this link to live example: https://codesandbox.io/p/sandbox/preprocesseditcellprops-bug-forked-2rmfqs
2. Click any "First name" cell once without activating edit mode
3. Press any key, app crashes with error `Cannot destructure property 'value' of 'params.props' as it is undefined.`

Note that if you set `age` column's `preProcessEditCellProps` to just return `return params;`, it still crashes but now you get internal datagrid error:
```ts
Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'value')
    at eval (https://2rmfqs.csb.app/node_modules/
mui/x-data-grid/esm/hooks/features/editing/useGridRowEditing.js:374:44
```


### Current behavior

If column definition has
1. `preProcessEditCellProps` defined
2. `editable: true`

and column cell is set as non-editable by DataGrid prop `isCellEditable` returning `false` for that field, `preProcessEditCellProps` is still called if user edits any cell by starting typing on cell before edit mode is activated.

This results in `params.props` being undefined (in `preProcessEditCellProps`) and causes app to crash.

This is extension of recently fixed bug https://github.com/mui/mui-x/issues/17298 

### Expected behavior

`preProcessEditCellProps` should not be called for the column if the cell in question is disabled via DataGrid's `isCellEditable` prop, even if column itself has `editable: true` set (I believe cell editability should have higher priority than column editability)

